Six people died after a Probox car and a pick-up collided on Meru-Mikinduri road in North Imenti, Meru county on Monday night. The driver of the Probox car and five passengers died instantly in the 9pm accident. A witness said the car, which had 15 passengers - being three times the required capacity, was speeding. North Imenti OCPD Sammy Kosgei said the driver attempted to overtake a lorry, leading to the crash. Gitonga Mugambi, Red Cross manager for Central and Eastern region, said seven people were rushed to hospital with serious injuries. He asked commuters to avoid boarding vehicles with excess passengers. Click here for the latest political news